    "severity": "high",
    "message": "New `redis-exporter` service is added to the prod observability stack, but `infra/observability/prometheus/prometheus.yml` has no `redis` scrape job (it scrapes only app, prometheus, otel-collector, postgres). The exporter exposes metrics on :9121 that nothing collects, so Redis remains effectively unobserved in prod despite the new service.",
    "suggestion": "Add a scrape_config to prometheus.yml, e.g.\n  - job_name: redis\n    static_configs:\n      - targets: [\"redis-exporter:9121\"]"
  },
  {
    "path": "infra/compose/observability.yml",
    "line": 94,
    "severity": "high",
    "message": "The new `redis-exporter` (and the Redis surface it monitors) has no alert rule. infra/observability/prometheus/alerts/ contains alertmanager/otel_collector/postgres/prometheus/slo rules but nothing for redis (e.g. redis down, exporter scrape failure, memory/eviction). Redis is a prod runtime dependency (redis-exporter depends_on: redis) being instrumented with no alerting wired up.",
    "suggestion": "Add infra/observability/prometheus/alerts/redis_alerts.yml with at least a RedisDown / RedisExporterScrapeFailed rule routed through the existing Alertmanager receiver, mirroring postgres_alerts.yml."
  },
  {
    "path": "infra/compose/observability.yml",
    "line": 94,
    "severity": "medium",
    "message": "No Grafana dashboard accompanies the new redis-exporter. infra/observability/grafana/dashboards/ has otel-collector/postgres/prometheus/slo JSON but no redis dashboard, so the collected Redis metrics (once scraped) have no panel. This breaks the alert↔dashboard parity maintained for every other scrape target.",
    "suggestion": "Add infra/observability/grafana/dashboards/redis.json with panels for the key redis_exporter series (up, memory, connected clients, evictions), consistent with postgres.json."
  }
